# CampuGrid — Implementation Plan

## Overview

CampuGrid is a distributed P2P compute marketplace that pools idle GPUs from student machines, making compute accessible to students who need it for ML training, 3D rendering, physics simulation, and data processing. This plan covers the full system: **Server**, **Client (Contributor)**, **Consumer Web App**, and **Marketing Website**.

---

## Locked Technical Decisions

| # | Decision | Answer | Rationale |
|---|----------|--------|-----------|
| 1 | Network model | **Hybrid** — `--network none` for render/data, Docker overlay for ML/sim | Maximum isolation for simple jobs, overlay only when inter-node comms needed |
| 2 | V1 workloads | **All 4** — rendering, data, ML, simulation | Full product from day 1 |
| 3 | ML sync | **Both DDP + Local SGD** — DDP premium (LAN only), Local SGD standard (WiFi) | Different pricing tiers, DDP has better convergence |
| 4 | Contributor app | **Tauri** (Rust + web frontend) | ~15MB, cross-platform, modern |
| 5 | Docker | **Bundled with Tauri installer**, images pulled per-workload | Frictionless onboarding |
| 6 | Redis HA | **Single instance** for MVP | Sentinel in V2 |
| 7 | Checkpointing | **Auto-inject** — no student code modification | Maintains zero-config promise |
| 8 | Deployment | **Laptop MVP** (24GB RAM, Ryzen 7 7840HS, RTX 4060) → GCP for prod | Docker Compose for dev, single VM for staging |
| 9 | OS support | **Linux + Windows** | Mac has no CUDA |
| 10 | Dockerfile gen | **Claude API** with aggressive caching | SHA-256 content hash cache |
| 11 | Web architecture | **Single Next.js app** — marketing + consumer app | Shared repo, route groups |
| 12 | Timeline | **~10 weeks** realistic (see phases below) | Not the 4-week fantasy from context.md |

