## System Architecture

### High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Consumer Side"
        WEB["Next.js Web App<br/>(Submit / Monitor / Results)"]
    end

    subgraph "Central Server (Your Laptop / GCP)"
        CADDY["Caddy<br/>Reverse Proxy + TLS"]
        API["FastAPI<br/>REST + WebSocket"]
        CELERY["Celery Workers<br/>AI Pipeline / Scheduler / Watchdog"]
        PG["PostgreSQL 16<br/>Source of Truth"]
        REDIS["Redis 7<br/>Queue / Pub-Sub / Heartbeats"]
        MINIO["MinIO<br/>Object Storage (S3)"]
        REGISTRY["Docker Registry v2<br/>Container Images"]
        KANIKO["Kaniko<br/>Rootless Image Builder"]
        PROM["Prometheus"]
        GRAF["Grafana + Loki"]
    end

    subgraph "Contributor Nodes"
        TAURI1["Tauri App<br/>+ Python Daemon<br/>+ Docker Runtime"]
        TAURI2["Tauri App<br/>+ Python Daemon<br/>+ Docker Runtime"]
        TAURI3["Tauri App<br/>+ Python Daemon<br/>+ Docker Runtime"]
    end

    WEB <-->|HTTPS + WSS| CADDY
    CADDY --> API
    API <--> REDIS
    API <--> PG
    API <--> MINIO
    CELERY <--> REDIS
    CELERY <--> PG
    CELERY <--> MINIO
    CELERY --> KANIKO
    KANIKO --> REGISTRY
    PROM --> GRAF

    TAURI1 <-->|WSS Persistent| API
    TAURI2 <-->|WSS Persistent| API
    TAURI3 <-->|WSS Persistent| API

    TAURI1 <-->|S3 API| MINIO
    TAURI2 <-->|S3 API| MINIO
    TAURI3 <-->|S3 API| MINIO

    TAURI1 -.->|"Docker overlay<br/>(ML/Sim only)"| TAURI2
    TAURI2 -.->|"Docker overlay<br/>(ML/Sim only)"| TAURI3
```

### Network Model Detail

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Rendering / Data Jobs"
        C1["Container<br/>--network none"]
        V1["/workspace volume<br/>(local disk)"]
        D1["Python Daemon<br/>(outside container)"]
        M1["MinIO"]

        C1 <--> V1
        D1 -->|"pre-download inputs<br/>to /workspace"| V1
        D1 -->|"post-upload outputs<br/>from /workspace"| M1
    end

    subgraph "ML Training / Simulation Jobs"
        C2["Container<br/>--network campugrid_overlay"]
        C3["Container<br/>--network campugrid_overlay"]
        M2["MinIO"]

        C2 <-->|"DDP all-reduce<br/>or MPI boundary"| C3
        C2 -->|"checkpoint upload"| M2
    end
```

**Key insight:** For `--network none` jobs, the **Python daemon** (running outside the container) handles all MinIO I/O. It pre-downloads inputs to a local volume, mounts that volume into the container, and post-uploads outputs after the container exits. The container never touches the network.

For ML/Sim jobs, containers join a **Docker overlay network** (`campugrid_overlay`) that only allows traffic between peer containers and MinIO. No internet access. Implemented via Docker network with `--internal` flag + explicit service connections.

