All server infrastructure runs via Docker Compose on your RTX 4060 laptop:

```yaml
# infra/docker-compose.yml
services:
  postgres:
    image: postgres:16-alpine
    environment:
      POSTGRES_DB: campugrid
      POSTGRES_USER: campugrid
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${PG_PASSWORD}
    ports: ["5432:5432"]
    volumes: ["pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data"]

  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine
    ports: ["6379:6379"]
    command: redis-server --maxmemory 512mb --maxmemory-policy allkeys-lru

  minio:
    image: minio/minio:latest
    command: server /data --console-address ":9001"
    environment:
      MINIO_ROOT_USER: campugrid
      MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD: ${MINIO_PASSWORD}
    ports: ["9000:9000", "9001:9001"]
    volumes: ["miniodata:/data"]

  registry:
    image: registry:2
    ports: ["5000:5000"]
    volumes: ["registrydata:/var/lib/registry"]

  prometheus:
    image: prom/prometheus:latest
    ports: ["9090:9090"]
    volumes: ["./prometheus/prometheus.yml:/etc/prometheus/prometheus.yml"]

  grafana:
    image: grafana/grafana:latest
    ports: ["3001:3000"]
    environment:
      GF_SECURITY_ADMIN_PASSWORD: ${GRAFANA_PASSWORD}

  loki:
    image: grafana/loki:latest
    ports: ["3100:3100"]

volumes:
  pgdata:
  miniodata:
  registrydata:
```

The FastAPI server + Celery workers run **natively** (not in Docker) during development for faster iteration:

```bash
# Terminal 1: FastAPI
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000

# Terminal 2: Celery worker (pipeline + scheduler)
celery -A app.celery_app worker --loglevel=info --concurrency=4

# Terminal 3: Celery beat (watchdog only)
celery -A app.celery_app beat --loglevel=info
```

Your laptop can also run as a **contributor node** simultaneously (for testing). The RTX 4060 becomes both the server AND a worker node.

---

## Implementation Phases

### Phase 1 — Foundation (Week 1–2)

**Goal:** A node can register, heartbeat, and the server can receive + store jobs.

| Task | Component | Details |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Docker Compose infra | infra/ | Postgres, Redis, MinIO, Registry up and running |
| FastAPI skeleton | server/ | Project structure, config, DB connection, health endpoint |
| SQLAlchemy models + Alembic | server/models/ | All 6 tables, initial migration |
| User auth | server/api/v1/ | JWT + OAuth2 Google SSO via NextAuth |
| WebSocket server | server/api/v1/websocket.py | Connection manager, room-based broadcasting |
| Node registration endpoint | server/api/v1/nodes.py | POST /nodes/register → issues cert, creates record |
| Heartbeat handler | server/api/v1/websocket.py | WS heartbeat → Redis sorted set |
| Job submission endpoint | server/api/v1/jobs.py | POST /jobs → upload to MinIO → create job record |
| **Testable outcome:** | | `curl POST /jobs` saves files to MinIO, node heartbeat visible in Redis |

---

### Phase 2 — AI Pipeline + Rendering (Week 3–4)

**Goal:** Drag a `.blend` file → system detects, splits, dispatches to a node, renders, assembles.

| Task | Component | Details |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Magic bytes detector | pipeline/detector.py | File signature matching + extension cross-check |
| Blend file analyzer | pipeline/analyzer.py | Parse .blend binary → frame range, render engine, VRAM est |
| Python AST analyzer | pipeline/analyzer.py | Import scanning, framework detection, GPU usage detection |
| Image catalog | pipeline/catalog.py | Dictionary lookup → Docker image for known combinations |
| Chunk splitter | pipeline/splitter.py | Frame-range splitting for render, byte-range for data |
| Pipeline orchestrator | pipeline/orchestrator.py | Celery task chaining: detect → analyze → catalog → split → queue |
| Event-driven scheduler | scheduler/matcher.py | On-chunk-queued dispatch, node scoring |
| Contributor daemon (Python) | client/daemon/ | agent.py, heartbeat.py, executor.py, storage_bridge.py |
| Storage bridge | client/daemon/storage_bridge.py | MinIO ↔ local volume for `--network none` containers |
| Render assembler | assembler/render_assembler.py | FFmpeg frame stitching |
| Build Blender Docker image | docker/images/blender-cycles/ | Pre-built, pushed to local registry |
| **Testable outcome:** | | Upload .blend → watch it split into chunks → renders on node → get back a video |

---

### Phase 3 — Fault Tolerance + Data Processing (Week 5–6)

**Goal:** Node goes offline → job recovers. CSV processing works end-to-end.

| Task | Component | Details |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Watchdog | scheduler/watchdog.py | 30s Celery beat, stale node detection, chunk rescue |
| Reliability scoring | models/node.py | Degradation on failure, recovery on success |
| Data processing splitter | pipeline/splitter.py | CSV byte-range sharding with clean row boundaries |
| Data assembler | assembler/data_assembler.py | Merge output shards |
| Claude Dockerfile gen | pipeline/generator.py | Prompt template, SHA-256 caching, Claude API call |
| Kaniko builder | pipeline/builder.py | Trigger build, track status, push to registry |
| Build python-data image | docker/images/python-data/ | Pre-built catalog image |
| **Testable outcome:** | | Submit CSV + transform script → processes → kill a node mid-job → recovers → result |

---

### Phase 4 — ML Training + Simulation (Week 7–8)

**Goal:** Distributed ML training works (both modes). Physics simulation works.

| Task | Component | Details |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Docker overlay network manager | client/daemon/network_manager.py | Create/join overlay for ML/sim jobs |
| Auto-checkpoint injection | docker/wrappers/ml_checkpoint_wrapper.py | Monkey-patch PyTorch optimizer |
| Local SGD implementation | docker/wrappers/local_sgd_wrapper.py | Periodic weight averaging |
| DDP orchestration | scheduler/dispatcher.py | Coordinate multi-node launch, torchrun setup |
| ML splitter | pipeline/splitter.py | Dataset row sharding |
| ML assembler | assembler/ml_assembler.py | Select best model weights, extract training curves |
| Simulation splitter | pipeline/splitter.py | Domain decomposition wrapper (OpenFOAM decomposePar) |
| Simulation assembler | assembler/sim_assembler.py | Domain reconstruction |
| Build PyTorch + OpenFOAM images | docker/images/ | Pre-built catalog images |
| ML sync mode selection | api/v1/jobs.py | User chooses Standard (Local SGD) vs Premium (DDP) |
| Network requirement enforcement | scheduler/matcher.py | LAN-only matching for DDP jobs |
| **Testable outcome:** | | Submit training script → trains across 2 nodes (Local SGD on WiFi) → get trained model + loss curve |

---

