---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- **Unit tests:** pytest for all server modules (pipeline, scheduler, watchdog, billing)
- **Integration tests:** Docker Compose up, submit real .blend file, verify output
- **WebSocket tests:** pytest-asyncio for WS connection, heartbeat, job dispatch
- **E2E browser test:** Browser subagent — login → upload → monitor → download

### Manual Verification
- **Fault tolerance demo:** Start 2 contributor nodes → submit render job → kill one node mid-job → verify chunk rescue → job completes
- **ML training demo:** Submit PyTorch script → verify distributed training across 2 nodes → verify auto-checkpoint → kill node → verify resume from checkpoint
- **Cross-platform:** Test Tauri installer on Linux and Windows

### Benchmarks
- **Scheduler latency:** Measure time from chunk queue to node dispatch (target: < 500ms)
- **Pipeline latency:** Measure time from file upload to first chunk dispatched (target: < 30s for catalog hits)
- **Throughput:** 50 concurrent simulated nodes, 10 simultaneous jobs

---

## Open Considerations (Non-Blocking)

> [!NOTE]
> These don't block implementation but should be decided before V2:
> - **Payment integration** (Stripe/Razorpay) for real-money payouts — V1 is gamification/credits only
> - **Campus SSO** specifics — which OAuth provider does your target campus use?
> - **Domain name** — needed before GCP deployment
> - **SSL certificates** — Caddy handles auto-TLS but needs a domain
> - **GDPR/data privacy** policy — important when handling student data across machines
